From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia

Mladen Žganjer (born 17 May 1966) is a Croatian professional football coach and former player. He currently serves as a goalkeeping coach for the Iran national football team under head coach Dragan Skočić.

## Career [ edit ]

Born in Rijeka, as a goalkeeper he spent much of his career with HNK Rijeka, playing in both the Yugoslav First League and Prva HNL. During the 1993-94 Prva HNL season he did not concede a goal for 622 minutes, making him the club's record holder in top tier competitions.[1] Before finishing his career, he played for SV Spittal in Austria, before returning to Croatia, where he played for NK Pomorac Kostrena.
